00053 void 
00054 Header::write(string path)
00055 {
00056     string output = path;
00057     
00058 #if BINARY_HEADER
00059     FILE *header = fopen((output.append(".hdt.header")).c_str(), "w+");
00060     
00061     // Graph parsing
00062     fwrite(&parsing,INT32,1,header);
00063     // Dictionary mapping
00064     fwrite(&mapping,INT32,1,header);
00065     // Dictionary separator
00066     fwrite(&d_separator,INT32,1,header);
00067     // Triples encoding
00068     fwrite(&t_encoding,INT32,1,header);
00069     
00070     // Statistics from the Dictionary
00071     fwrite(&nsubjects,INT32,1,header);
00072     fwrite(&npredicates,INT32,1,header);
00073     fwrite(&nobjects,INT32,1,header);
00074     fwrite(&ssubobj,INT32,1,header);
00075     
00076     // Triples in the dataset
00077     fwrite(&ntriples,INT32,1,header);
00078     
00079     fclose(header);
00080 #else
00081     ofstream headerfile( (output.append(".hdt.header")).c_str());
00082     
00083     headerfile
00084     << "Parsing: " << parsing << endl
00085     << "Mapping: " << mapping << endl
00086     << "Separator: " << d_separator << endl
00087     << "Encoding: " << t_encoding << endl
00088     << "NSubjects: " << nsubjects << endl
00089     << "NPredicates: " << npredicates << endl
00090     << "NObjects: " << nobjects << endl
00091     << "NShared: " << ssubobj << endl
00092     << "Triples: " << ntriples << endl
00093     << "NLiterals: " << nliterals << endl
00094     << "Nentries: " << nentries << endl;
00095     
00096     headerfile.close();
00097 #endif
00098 }

00100 void 
00101 Header::read(string path)
00102 {
00103     string output = path;
00104     
00105 #if BINARY_HEADER
00106     FILE *header = fopen((output.append(".hdt.header")).c_str(), "r");
00107     
00108     if (header==NULL) {
00109       cout << "Exception while reading Header in "<<output<<".\n";
00110       exit(1);
00111     }
00112     size_t t = 0;
00113 
00114     // Graph parsing
00115     t += fread(&parsing,INT32,1,header);
00116     // Dictionary mapping
00117     t += fread(&mapping,INT32,1,header);
00118     // Dictionary separator
00119     t += fread(&d_separator,INT32,1,header);
00120     // Triples encoding
00121     t += fread(&t_encoding,INT32,1,header);
00122     
00123     // Dictionary stats
00124     t += fread(&nsubjects,INT32,1,header);
00125     // Dictionary mapping
00126     t += fread(&npredicates,INT32,1,header);
00127     // Dictionary separator
00128     t += fread(&nobjects,INT32,1,header);
00129     // Triples encoding
00130     t += fread(&ssubobj,INT32,1,header);
00131     
00132      // Triples in the dataset
00133     t += fread(&ntriples,INT32,1,header);
00134     
00135     if (t != 9)
00136     {
00137         cout << "   <ERROR> Errors in Header" << endl;
00138         exit(1);
00139     }
00140     
00141     fclose(header);
00142 #else
00143     try
00144     {
00145         ifstream headerfile( (output.append(".hdt.header")).c_str());
00146         
00147         if(headerfile.good()) {
00148             string line;
00149             
00150             getline(headerfile, line, ' ');
00151             headerfile >> parsing;
00152             
00153             getline(headerfile, line, ' ');
00154             headerfile >> mapping;
00155             
00156             getline(headerfile, line, ' ');
00157             headerfile >> d_separator;
00158             
00159             getline(headerfile, line, ' ');
00160             headerfile >> t_encoding;
00161             
00162             getline(headerfile, line, ' ');
00163             headerfile >> nsubjects;
00164             
00165             getline(headerfile, line, ' ');
00166             headerfile >> npredicates;
00167             
00168             getline(headerfile, line, ' ');
00169             headerfile >> nobjects;
00170             
00171             getline(headerfile, line, ' ');
00172             headerfile >> ssubobj;
00173             
00174             getline(headerfile, line, ' ');
00175             headerfile >> ntriples;
00176             
00177             getline(headerfile, line, ' ');
00178             headerfile >> nliterals;
00179             
00180             getline(headerfile, line, ' ');
00181             headerfile >> nentries;
00182         }
00183         
00184         headerfile.close();
00185     }
00186     catch(const ios::failure &problem)
00187     {
00188         // Something really went wrong here
00189         cout << "Error reading header " << problem.what();
00190     }
00191 #endif
00192 }
